      "content": "hey, i'm working on this historical fiction novel set in the deep south during the 1950s, specifically in alabama. i want to make it feel really raw and grounded in the actual tension of that time period. can you help me brainstorm some ways to establish a heavy, oppressive atmosphere in a scene involving the local social hierarchies? i want the reader to feel exactly how much danger certain characters were in just by the way people spoke to them.",
